comments.body:
Thanks for reaching out!  There is a long history behind how Buildah and Podman handle multi-arch images.  Many multi-arch images do not declare the architectures (and variants) correctly which lead to a variety of issues.

In case of `--pull=never`, however, the user requests to not pull an image at all and I sympathize with the idea to not override the pull policy in this specific case.

@rhatdan @nalind WDYT?
